ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Obviously for people who are required to take this course, it's a no brainer - but it's certainly not a hardship, as Irina is probably the best Russian instructor at Yale. That said, the enjoyment (and learning) you actually get out of the class depends a lot on your classmates, as discussion and conversation are very important components of the class.
One question: Do you want russian women/men to fall in love with you?
